  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The 'Personalize My treatment' (PMT) platform is a novel form of biobanking in which cancer
      patients willingly consent to provide residual, clinical samples (surplus after diagnostic
      testing) of their tumors for cancer research, to give access to their medical record for data
      collection and then followed prospectively throughout the trajectory of their illness. They
      further willingly consent to be recontacted for being informed of other research projects,
      including clinical trials.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
